  "texts": [
    "Each new generation of mobile technology has promoted advances in digital education, such as virtual platforms and simulators.",
    "5G, in particular, facilitates communication between AI and the Internet of Things, allowing efficient data management crucial for AI development.",
    "This technology reconfigures work and business, directly impacting education by distributing tasks between humans and machines.On the other hand, García-Sánchez [31] highlights the increasing use of online educational platforms and chatbots, like ChatGPT, which enhance the learning experience by providing personalized and detailed responses.",
    "While these tools transform teaching and foster student engagement, they also present ethical and practical challenges, such as information reliability and data privacy.",
    "García-Peñalvo [32] emphasizes the need to understand how students perceive and use these technologies before their widespread adoption.According to the research developed by García-Peñalvo [33], there is a shift in social perception of AI following the advent of ChatGPT."
  ],
